Sentencas: As a promising electrolyte material for solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs), BaZr0.1Ce0.7Y0.1Yb0.1O3-delta (BZCYYb) often surfers from its high sintering temperature, which causes Ba evaporation and sluggish grain growth, thus reducing the electrical conductivity.
Titulo: Microwave sintering of high-performance BaZr0.1Ce0.7Y0.1Yb0.1O3-δ (BZCYYb) electrolytes for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: In this work, densified BZCYYb electrolytes were fabricated at temperatures as low as 1400 degrees C using the microwave sintering technique.
Titulo: Microwave sintering of high-performance BaZr0.1Ce0.7Y0.1Yb0.1O3-δ (BZCYYb) electrolytes for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Comparing with the conventional sintered ones, a temperature decrease of 150 degrees C is achieved.
Titulo: Microwave sintering of high-performance BaZr0.1Ce0.7Y0.1Yb0.1O3-δ (BZCYYb) electrolytes for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The Ba evaporation is effectively suppressed, and large grain sizes of similar to 4 mu m are obtained.
Titulo: Microwave sintering of high-performance BaZr0.1Ce0.7Y0.1Yb0.1O3-δ (BZCYYb) electrolytes for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The total conductivity for microwave sintered symmetric cell measured in wet air at 700 degrees C is 3.8 x 10(-2)
Titulo: Microwave sintering of high-performance BaZr0.1Ce0.7Y0.1Yb0.1O3-δ (BZCYYb) electrolytes for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Titulo: Microwave sintering of high-performance BaZr0.1Ce0.7Y0.1Yb0.1O3-δ (BZCYYb) electrolytes for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells
